Ensure that you sleep enough and that you have a good quality sleep should be a student’s “secret weapon” to fight stress, fatigue and anxiety, signals. Even avoid getting fat, as lack of sleep causes the brain to enter in inanitation mode, which makes it hungry constantly.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old Californian who studied chemistry and physics, helped Professor Czeisler design the course after attending one of his classes last year during his first year at Harvard.
